Build a Next.js 15 App Router project for NeuralOps — an AI workspace platform.

## PRINCIPLES (non-negotiable, apply everywhere)

1. All API calls go in /src/services/ — one file per domain. Zero fetch() calls inside components.
2. Use TanStack Query for all server data. Components never call fetch directly.
3. Auth token lives in Zustand (authStore). The base API client attaches it automatically to every request.
4. Use shadcn/ui for all UI components. Do not invent custom components when a shadcn one exists.
5. CSS variables for all colors — never hardcode hex. Theme changes happen in globals.css only.
6. TypeScript everywhere. No .js files.
7. Keep components small and single-purpose. If a component grows beyond ~100 lines, split it.
8. Base API URL always from: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL

## TECH STACK

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js 15 (App Router) |
| Language | TypeScript |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui |
| Server state | TanStack Query |
| Client state | Zustand |
| HTTP client | Native fetch (wrapped in api.client.ts) |
| Streaming | Native EventSource (SSE) |
| Icons | Lucide React |
| Forms | React Hook Form + Zod |

## THEME

Feel: clean, minimal, professional — like ChatGPT or Linear. Generous white space. Nothing feels cramped.

Define all colors in globals.css as CSS variables:

:root {
  --background: #ffffff;
  --background-subtle: #f9fafb;
  --foreground: #111827;
  --foreground-muted: #6b7280;
  --primary: #7c3aed;
  --primary-hover: #6d28d9;
  --primary-foreground: #ffffff;
  --primary-tint: #f5f3ff;
  --border: #e5e7eb;
  --border-strong: #d1d5db;
  --input: #ffffff;
  --ring: #7c3aed;
  --card: #ffffff;
  --sidebar: #f9fafb;
  --muted: #f3f4f6;
  --muted-foreground: #9ca3af;
}

Typography:
- Font: Inter (Google Fonts)
- Base size: 14px, headings semibold, line height 1.6

Components:
- Buttons: rounded-md, violet primary, ghost secondary
- Inputs: rounded-md, subtle border, violet focus ring
- Sidebar items: px-3 py-2, rounded-md on hover/active, icon + label
- Cards: white background, subtle border, rounded-lg, no heavy shadows
- Modals: centered, rounded-xl, soft backdrop

RULE: Components always use var(--variable-name). Never raw hex, never hardcoded Tailwind colors.

## PROJECT STRUCTURE

src/
├── app/                    # pages and layouts
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                 # shadcn components only
│   ├── layout/             # AppShell, Sidebar, TopBar
│   ├── auth/               # login/signup/invite forms
│   ├── chat/               # chat area (leave renderers as placeholders)
│   └── shared/             # reusable pieces used across pages
├── services/               # ALL API calls
│   ├── api.client.ts
│   ├── auth.service.ts
│   ├── companies.service.ts
│   ├── users.service.ts
│   ├── projects.service.ts
│   ├── channels.service.ts
│   ├── topics.service.ts
│   ├── messages.service.ts
│   ├── agents.service.ts
│   ├── personas.service.ts
│   ├── ai-models.service.ts
│   ├── mcp-servers.service.ts
│   ├── knowledge-base.service.ts
│   └── notifications.service.ts
├── store/
│   ├── auth.store.ts       # token, user, currentCompany
│   └── ui.store.ts         # activeTopicId, sidebar state
├── hooks/                  # TanStack Query hooks
└── types/                  # shared TypeScript interfaces

## SERVICE FILES

Generate each service file as an empty shell with typed function signatures only — no implementation. I will implement the actual API calls separately.

## APP SHELL

Generate auth pages (login, signup) and the main app shell only:

- /login and /signup — clean centered forms
- /app — left sidebar (260px) + main content area
  - Sidebar: company name + switcher at top, project → channel → topic tree (expandable, + buttons to add each level), notification bell + settings + user avatar at bottom
  - Top bar: breadcrumb, search icon
  - Content area: empty placeholder — pages will be added one by one

## PLACEHOLDER COMPONENTS

Leave these as empty divs with a data-component attribute. Do not implement them:

- ChatMessageList
- ChatMessageItem
- StreamingIndicator
- TextRenderer
- CodeRenderer
- GraphRenderer
- TerminalRenderer
- FormRenderer
- WebRenderer

## EXPANDABILITY RULE

Any new page, modal, or feature added in future automatically follows the same patterns. New pages import from /services. New components use shadcn. New colors use CSS variables. Nothing special needed to stay consistent.

Generate .env.local.example with NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

Push to GitHub when done.